In order to represent a wide range of today's GGBS compositions, 16 different slags were selected from the FEhS database (FEhS – Institut für Baustoff-Forschung e.V., Duisburg, Germany). Chemical composition was measured on fused tabs by XRF (Panalytical Zetium). The composition was calculated conventionally as oxides (Table 1
                        ). Major element compositions and maximum values from literature are displayed in Fig. 1
                        . CaO contents in our dataset are between 29.0 and 43.2 wt%. The lowest value is lower than lowest values reported in literature, but the highest value is also 4.3 wt% lower than maxima reported [1]. Most GGBS in our dataset contain between 40 and 42 wt% CaO. SiO2 contents in our GGBS set range from 34.6 to 39.2 wt%, a distribution that is on both ends about 2% smaller than the extreme values for GGBS from different regions of the world reported in Matthes et al. (2018) [1]. For Al2O3 the observed concentrations range between 6.8 and 20.1 wt%, which corresponds to extreme values reported in literature [1]. However, only GGBS 15 attains such a high Al2O3 content (20.1 wt%), the next lower sample (GGBS 14) contains 13.7 wt% Al2O3. The majority of selected GGBS contain between 10 and 12 wt% Al2O3. MgO contents in our sample set are between 6.12 and 11.6 wt%, both extrema are 3 wt% below extreme values reported by Matthes et al. (2018) [1]. In the studied GGBS, TiO2 contents range for 0.27 to 3.02 wt%, with 3.02 wt% of TiO2 in GGBS 9. The extreme values again correspond to the values observed by Matthes et al. (2018) [1]. In contrast, most GGBS contain between 0.5 and 1 wt% TiO2. Reactivity indices were calculated according to the composition data.
